<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE60FF95D6DCFE20FDC49C43" blockId="5.[174,1233,399,778]" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">
Diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE60FF95D740FE20FDD59FC0" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[383,575,399,425]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hippai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE60FF95D740FE20FDD59FC0" box="[383,575,399,425]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">Nediphya hippai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE60FF95D479FE20FD6E9FC3" box="[582,644,399,426]" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE60FF95D481FE3FFCCB9FC0" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[702,801,399,425]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lyleae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE60FF95D481FE3FFCCB9FC0" box="[702,801,399,425]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">N. lyleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE60FF95D517FE20FC8C9FC0" box="[808,870,399,426]" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
have similar carapace banding patterns and white spotted abdomens. The two species can be distinguished by epigynal median plates (
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE60FF95D75EFE7FFE639F80" box="[353,393,464,489]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">Mp</emphasis>
) (wider than long in 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE60FF95D4BEFE7FFD079F80" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[641,749,463,489]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hippai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE60FF95D4BEFE7FFD079F80" box="[641,749,463,489]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">N. hippai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE60FF95D4CBFE60FCDB9F83" box="[756,817,463,490]" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE60FF95D507FE7FFCA59F80" box="[824,847,464,489]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">vs</emphasis>
. longer than wide in 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE60FF95D279FE7FFB439F80" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[1094,1193,463,489]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lyleae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE60FF95D279FE7FFB439F80" box="[1094,1193,463,489]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">N. lyleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE60FF95D290FE60FF2E9C63" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(cf. 
<figureCitation id="A5FF0A8EDE60FF95D6C7FE40FE199C63" box="[248,499,495,522]" captionStart="Figs 40–51" captionStartId="9.[174,213,1747,1769]" captionTargetBox="[189,1210,673,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-133@9.[189,1210,673,1697]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 40–51. Epigynes of Nediphya hippai sp. n. (40–41, 46, 49), N. padillai sp. n. (42), N. lehtineni (43, 50–51), N. lyleae sp. n. (44–45, 48) and Diphya macrophthalma (47). Scale = 0.2 mm. Abbreviations: Cd copulatory ducts, Er elongate anterior receptacles, Mp median plate, Re round proper receptacles, Rr round anterior receptacles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454201/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">figs 40–41 and 44–45</figureCitation>
)) and femoral spines (lacking in 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE60FF95D549FE5FFC089C60" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[886,994,495,521]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hippai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE60FF95D549FE5FFC089C60" box="[886,994,495,521]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">N. hippai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE60FF95D5D6FE40FBCD9C63" box="[1001,1063,495,522]" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE60FF95D210FE5FFBA79C60" box="[1071,1101,496,521]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">vs.</emphasis>
present on femora I and II in 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE60FF95D7BAFDBFFE039C40" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[389,489,527,553]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lyleae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE60FF95D7BAFDBFFE039C40" box="[389,489,527,553]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">N. lyleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE60FF95D7CFFDA0FDC49C43" box="[496,558,527,554]" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE60FF95D6DCFD80FEBF9D63" blockId="5.[174,1233,399,778]" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">
D e s c r i p t i o n. Female 
<typeStatus id="E27FA8A9DE60FF95D43FFD80FD809C23" box="[512,618,559,586]" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">holotype</typeStatus>
. Total length 2.42, carapace 1.08 long, 0.78 wide. Carapace light yellow with dark V-mark. Clypeus blackish. Chelicerae yellow with longitudinal blackish stripes proximally. Sternum, maxillae and labium yellow. Legs yellow. Femora, tibiae, metatarsi grayish distally. Abdomen dorsally dark yellow with light longitudinal band and indistinct transversal stripes and covered with numerous white guanine spots. Abdomen somewhat darker laterally. Abdomen yellow ventrally, without any markings.
</paragraph>
<caption id="69BB4683DE60FF95D695F8A7FE7D9950" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454193" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6454193" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454193/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" startId="5.[170,209,1800,1822]" targetBox="[195,1204,801,1771]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE60FF95D695F8A7FE7D9950" blockId="5.[170,1228,1800,1849]" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">
Figs 9–15. Somatic characters of 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE60FF95D43DF8A7FD019974" authorityName="Nicolet" authorityYear="1849" box="[514,747,1800,1821]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Diphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrophthalma">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE60FF95D43DF8A7FD019974" box="[514,747,1800,1821]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">Diphya macrophthalma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(9–11), 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE60FF95D578F8A7FBEB9974" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[839,1025,1800,1821]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lehtineni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE60FF95D578F8A7FBEB9974" box="[839,1025,1800,1821]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">Nediphya lehtineni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE60FF95D232F8A7FBAC9977" box="[1037,1094,1800,1822]" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(12–13) and 
