<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE63FF96D6E4FDD6FB989CBD" blockId="6.[166,1225,633,915]" pageId="6" pageNumber="209">
Epigyne as in 
<figureCitation id="A5FF0A8EDE63FF96D747FDD6FDD49CFD" box="[376,574,633,660]" captionStart="Figs 40–51" captionStartId="9.[174,213,1747,1769]" captionTargetBox="[189,1210,673,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-133@9.[189,1210,673,1697]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 40–51. Epigynes of Nediphya hippai sp. n. (40–41, 46, 49), N. padillai sp. n. (42), N. lehtineni (43, 50–51), N. lyleae sp. n. (44–45, 48) and Diphya macrophthalma (47). Scale = 0.2 mm. Abbreviations: Cd copulatory ducts, Er elongate anterior receptacles, Mp median plate, Re round proper receptacles, Rr round anterior receptacles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454201/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="209">figs 40–41, 46, 49</figureCitation>
; median plate wider than long with distinct sulci directed laterally from copulatory openings, sclerotized copulatory ducts short; receptacles tear-drop shaped. 
<typeStatus id="E27FA8A9DE63FF96D73BFD16FE839CBD" box="[260,361,697,724]" pageId="6" pageNumber="209">Paratype</typeStatus>
female with broken off tip of embolus in left receptacle (
<figureCitation id="A5FF0A8EDE63FF96D5D2FD16FB8C9CBD" box="[1005,1126,697,724]" captionStart="Figs 40–51" captionStartId="9.[174,213,1747,1769]" captionTargetBox="[189,1210,673,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-133@9.[189,1210,673,1697]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 40–51. Epigynes of Nediphya hippai sp. n. (40–41, 46, 49), N. padillai sp. n. (42), N. lehtineni (43, 50–51), N. lyleae sp. n. (44–45, 48) and Diphya macrophthalma (47). Scale = 0.2 mm. Abbreviations: Cd copulatory ducts, Er elongate anterior receptacles, Mp median plate, Re round proper receptacles, Rr round anterior receptacles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454201/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="209">figs 41, 49</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE63FF96D6E4FD76FE7F9C9D" blockId="6.[166,1225,633,915]" box="[219,405,729,756]" pageId="6" pageNumber="209">Male unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE63FF96D6E4FD56FD8C9D5D" blockId="6.[166,1225,633,915]" pageId="6" pageNumber="209">
Distribution. The new species is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="E27FA8A9DE63FF96D54DFD56FC4E9D7D" box="[882,932,761,788]" pageId="6" pageNumber="209">type</typeStatus>
locality, where 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE63FF96D266FD56FEE69D5A" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lehtineni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE63FF96D266FD56FEE69D5A" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="209">Nediphya lehtineni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE63FF96D72CFCB6FEBB9D5D" box="[275,337,793,820]" pageId="6" pageNumber="209" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is also known to occur.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE63FF96D6E4FC96FCED9D1D" blockId="6.[166,1225,633,915]" pageId="6" pageNumber="209">
E t y m o l o g y. 
<location id="381B40D0DE63FF96D7BEFC96FE479D3D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:B56DA71DDE60FF96D691FF60FCED9D1D:381B40D0DE63FF96D7BEFC96FE479D3D" box="[385,429,825,852]" country="Finland" county="Turku" municipality="Heikki Hippa" name="The" pageId="6" pageNumber="209">The</location>
species name is a patronym in honour of our senior colleague 
<collectingMunicipality id="DD1F8C71DE63FF96D246FC96FF1A9D1D" pageId="6" pageNumber="209">Heikki Hippa</collectingMunicipality>
(
<collectingCounty id="D41A6E87DE63FF96D6C0FCF6FEA49D1D" box="[255,334,857,884]" pageId="6" pageNumber="209">Turku</collectingCounty>
, 
<collectingCountry id="45D3569BDE63FF96D766FCF6FE5C9D1D" box="[345,438,857,884]" name="Finland" pageId="6" pageNumber="209">Finland</collectingCountry>
) who collected the 
<typeStatus id="E27FA8A9DE63FF96D4A6FCF6FCE99D1D" box="[665,771,857,884]" pageId="6" pageNumber="209">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
